<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0jjeOYMjmDU" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0"></iframe>

<p>in which he explains <a href="https://io9.gizmodo.com/scientists-still-puzzled-by-a-fractal-discovered-500-ye-5864577" target="_blank">tree branching structures</a> and<br />
writes a <strong>recursion</strong> in his own JavaScript library: <a href="https://p5js.org/" target="_blank"><strong>p5.js</strong></a></p>

<p><span class="fragment"><span style="color: tomato;"><em>You <strong>don’t</strong> need to know <strong>p5.js</strong> to understand this video!</em></span></span></p>

