<p><span class="fragment"><span style="color: tomato;"><em>You <strong>might very well</strong> be quizzed or tested on them…</em></span></span></p>

<hr />

<h3 id="so-to-summarize">So, to summarize:</h3>

<p><span class="fragment"><strong>For loops</strong> and <strong>while loops</strong> are both <em><strong>iterative</strong>.</em></span></p>

<p><span class="fragment">A <strong>while loop</strong> is like a <strong>for loop</strong> with a <strong>conditional statement</strong>.</span></p>

<p><span class="fragment"><strong>Self-similarity</strong> is when <em>parts</em> bear resemblance to the <em>whole.</em></span></p>

<p><span class="fragment"><strong>Recursion</strong> is something that’s defined <em>in terms of itself.</em></span></p>

<p><span class="fragment">A <strong>Recursive function</strong> includes a <strong>call</strong> <em>to itself,</em> producing results that are <em>similar</em> but <em>not identical.</em></span></p>

